<AuthorizeView>
    <Authorized>
        <main>
            <div class="p-lg-5 mb-4 bg-white rounded-3 d-lg-flex">
            <div class="container-fluid py-5 w-auto">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold">How to upload</h1>
                <p class="col-md-12 font-11">
                    The first thing you want to do is ensure that no unwanted data is in the directory you want to upload.
                    Once that is done you want to create a .zip archive in the root directory of your project containing all the files and subdirectories of your project. (see the pictures on the right).
                    <br/>It is important that the archive does not contain a folder with your project inside it. (see the pictures below)
                </p>
                <div class="d-lg-flex">
                    <figure class="figure f1 rounded border-danger">
                        <figcaption class="figure-caption text-center pt-2 text-danger fw-bold">Not like this</figcaption>
                        <img src="/img/not_like_this_2.png" class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" alt="...">

                    </figure>                            
                    <figure class="figure f2 rounded border-success">
                        <figcaption class="figure-caption text-center pt-2 text-success fw-bold">Like this</figcaption>
                        <img src="/img/like_this.png" class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" alt="...">
                    </figure>                    
                    <figure class="figure f2 rounded border-primary px-2 py-1" style="margin-left: auto; margin-right: 3rem; height: fit-content">
                        <figcaption class="figure-caption text-center pt-2 text-primary">Make sure to select <i class="fw-bold">ZIP</i></figcaption>
                        <img src="/img/format-zip.png" class="figure-img img-fluid rounded" alt="...">
                    </figure>
                </div>

            </div>
                <div class="card text-center my-auto">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <ul class="nav nav-tabs card-header-tabs" id="myTab" role="tablist">
                            <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
                                <button class="nav-link active" id="w11-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#w11" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="w11" aria-selected="true">Windows 11</button>
                            </li>
                            <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
                                <button class="nav-link" id="w10-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#w10" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="w10" aria-selected="false">Windows 10</button>
                            </li>
                            <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
                                <button class="nav-link" id="contact-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#contact" type="button" role="tab" aria-controls="contact" aria-selected="false">Outcome</button>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div class="tab-content" id="myTabContent">
                        <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="w11" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="w11-tab">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">Creating .zip archive on Windows 11</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">With supporting text below as a natural lead-in to additional content.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="frame" style="height: 340px; overflow: hidden;">
                                <img src="img/howToZipW11.png" class="card-img-bottom" alt="...">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="w10" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="w10-tab">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">Creating .zip archive on Windows 10 (<a href="https://www.win-rar.com/" target="_blank">WinRAR</a>)</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">With supporting text below as a natural lead-in to additional content.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="frame" style="height: 340px; overflow: hidden;">
                                <img src="img/howToZipW10.png" class="card-img-bottom" alt="...">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="contact" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="contact-tab">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">The structure is important!</h5>
                                <p class="card-text">This is what your zip archive should look like when opened.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="frame" style="height: 340px; overflow: hidden;">
                                <img src="img/outcome.png" class="card-img-bottom img-white" alt="...">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
                
            </div>

            <div class="row align-items-lg-stretch pb-4">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="h-100 p-5 text-white bg-primary rounded-3">
                        <h2>Upload</h2>
                        <p>
                            Once the project is correctly archived in a .zip format you can go ahead and upload it. <br/>
                            The upload time might vary depending on the size of the project. <br/> <br/>
                        </p>
                        <a href="Upload"><button class="btn btn-outline-light" type="button">Upload</button></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="h-100 p-5 bg-white border rounded-3">
                        <h2>Visit you website</h2>
                        <p>
                            The project will be uploaded on a different volume on this web server and can be visited on a sub-domain. <br/>
                            All hosting is free but you are responsible for the content you upload, if you wish to permanently remove something you have uploaded contact the website administrator.
                        </p>
                        <a href="https://pages.win21.pingu.onl"><button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" type="button">Browse websites</button></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>
    </Authorized>
    <NotAuthorized>
        <div class="info-box">
            <div class="alert alert-warning d-flex align-items-center" role="alert">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill flex-shrink-0 me-2" viewBox="0 0 16 16" role="img" aria-label="Warning:">
